				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">So Bards arent the only ones with problems....<a name="62409"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 16 04 11:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I my quest to spread discord across the web about the task system I ran across this on the rangers site.
<br />

<br />
Quote: 
<br />
I do appreciate everyone taking the time to gather the input of the ranger regulars on this board, however, we are not going to be changing the epic at this point folks. I understand that this is not what many of you want to hear, likewise there are many that this will come as good news to. 
<br />

<br />
One of the key problems is this schism in the ranger community. Rangers are very passionate one way or the other, so much so that you flame and torment each other on the issue. We have made the decision that we will be focusing on melee for rangers, let that be the start of definition. This does not mean archery will go away nor that it will be nerfed into extinction. We would like to focus on your melee skills. So with that in mind, where do you want to go from here? Knowing that melee will be your primary focus, what would you like to see tweaked, poked and prodded for the ranger class? 
<br />
Message Edited by Brenlo on 09-15-2004 01:44 PM 
<br />

<br />
Brenlo Bixiebopper 
<br />
Community Relations Manager 
<br />

<br />
--------------------------------------------- 
<br />
Halfling, Cajun Style! 
<br />

<br />
I was under the impression that post 55 rangers were given the eq directive that archery was their thing...who knew? 
<br />

<br />
I am not sure (having a ranger) that I even find this humurous. Someone must have found a really good and profitable use for dead rangers.
<br />

<br />
I am just wondering if there is a similar bard post coming....
<br />

<br />
Edit: I am about as guilty as anyone, but maybe its time we all tried a little harder for a unified front? We don't have to agree on everything, just support  each other a little more?
<br />

<br />
Or not?</span></td>
