				<td colspan="2"><span>SOE announced a while ago that they want rangers to be up close and personal with the mobs as much as possible. When they first showed the new epics (pictures taken at the guild summit) they had a bow. Of course the rangers were psyched, since they figured a really nice bow should've been their first epic. Well, at the last minute, after SOE made the &quot;You'll be a low DPS rogue without BS, and archery sucks&quot; announcement they changed the epic to a sword. So, yeah, it sucks losing AE kiting, not the primary focus of the class, for a certain percentage of bards, but it must REALLY suck losing the primary focus for everyone in a class. All rangers over 60 have spent a lot of AA's to get their archery where it is, and now their being told it doesn't matter. It's kinda of like if they were to tell us &quot;IM3 and SM3 (and the like) won't stack with any other mods anymore, but you aren't getting any AA refunds...&quot;</span></td>
