				<td colspan="2"><span>I think with a class as diverse as bards, it will be nigh impossible to get everyone to agree on what we want.
<br />

<br />
As noted above, rangers can argue melee vs archery.  But bards are so multifaceted that I think the one thing we can be sure to agree on is: we (bards) want to be wanted, and useful in all situations.  I'm sure most classes feel that way.
<br />

<br />
We don't have it as bad as warriors, berserkers, and perhaps shaman do in terms of usefulness.  Granted each of them has their place, but it's more limited than ours (even after the OoW Nerf Expansion).
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
